author: Muhammad Zulfadly Bin Abdul Manap
text: The location is quite convenient especially if you're those who like to workout during the weekend and go shopping/eating out at town after. The staff is friendly. Plenty of machine varieties suitable for bodybuilding or powerlifting. The free weights area might be a bit cramped, but thank God the squat racks/lifting platforms are not. The changing rooms are well-equipped with toiletries.

author: Naveen Vasudevan
text: AF Orchard is conveniently located near public transport and surrounded by plenty of restaurants, making it easy to fit workouts into a busy schedule. The gym is well-equipped with properly maintained machines and clean, modern facilities including toilets and lockers. Experienced trainers are always on hand to offer guidance and support. Equipment is handled with care, and the overall environment is safe and welcoming. The support staffs are welcoming and approachable.

author: chat noir wow
text:
Update 6 April: I‚Äôm so glad that they managed to get the air con back for the cardio area. It is now so comforting to run at AF orchard, no other AFs have such pleasant air con for running. It keeps the humidity low and easier for breathing.

I've been coming to AF Orchard for runs on treadmill. The air con used to be good for 10km runs. However, the staff mentioned that the reason for the weak air con at the cardio area is run by the management. While there are fans, but the air remain hot and humid at the treadmills area. I have also observed other runners checking out which treadmill has better ventilation. But they are mostly similar in terms of temperature and ventilation. Otherwise, the staff are great! I once forgot my hair band and the staff gave me hers. ‚ù§Ô∏è The space is perfect, not claustrophobic. If the air con temperature could be cooler, this will be the best gym I visited among AF. They also have members treat!

author: Taylor L
text: I tried it for a day with a free trial. First of all, the location was perfect, as it's connected to the MRT. The gym was a bit smaller than I expected, but it was clean. The staff was friendly and helpful.

author: Suf
text: Gym is equipped with many of the machines I find useful and the crowd is pretty okay, even during peak hours. Well-maintained and furnished with gorgeous decor and goodies for members from time to time. Highly recommended.

author: Ahmad Taufiq Muhammad
text:

Positives

Some negatives

author: Jeremy Chan
text:
My 1st time coming to this AF gym & I must say, definitely not disappointed. All the AF gyms that are pretty much central; city area; have proven to be more than adequate for a fruitful workout. They have all the necessary equipment required for a great work out.

Top 3 AF gyms for me in Singapore are pretty much all in the main city, lol. City Hall, Wheelock, & this Orchard Gateway/313 outlet. This definitely won‚Äôt be the last time I hit this gym. I‚Äôm just glad my 3 favorite AF gyms are all close to where I reside.

5 outta 5 stars for this gym as well!

P.S. This gym & the Wheelock branch have nice views, this one more right smack on Orchard though hahaha.

author: Lucien Lim
text:
A great branch of AF that has an excellent location and friendly staff! It is clean and well maintained, and has most of the equipment one would need.

The only downside to this gym is also it‚Äôs plus, that being it‚Äôs good location. Situated on the 4th floor of Orchard Gateway, it‚Äôs a convenient 5 min walk from Somerset MRT, making it busy/crowded even at 11pm. This can be an issue as one would have to wait a while to use the equipment.

author: K T
text: me and my friend took the empty hip thrust machine (no weights on it) and a PT came up to us and said he was using it for his client, this just seems like he is using his power to get us to leave the machine so he can use for his client... so rude that he lied and cannot just be frank about wanting to use, if he asked nicely instead of saying oh im using this, we would not have felt angry

author: John Ko
text: Anytime Fitness Orchard is too cheap to turn on their AC to help ventilate, allowing its members to cool down. Damn they won‚Äôt even turn their fans on. Avoid this gym unless you love working out in a sauna.

author: Munny L
text:
Located on level 4 after the concierge on the right, in Orchard Central.

One of the best anytime fitness gym experiences, ample of workout equipment, 2 squat racks!

Great view overlooking orchard road (not pictured) and Dyson hairdryers at the shower rooms. Lots of lockers for you to pick from! Finally can workout in orchard central.

About 20-25 pax on a Saturday,  lunchtime workout.

Open 24/7! Staff hours are till 10pm daily.

Missing a shaker or forgot a tee? Anytime has got your back with 5 colours to choose from, I had to refrain from buying too many shakers.

I think it just lacked the vending machine with the protein shakes though, it's more convenient!

author: Sihan Goi
text:
Pretty good gym with ample strength equipment even though it's not very big (2 platforms, 2 power racks, 1 half rack, 6 regular Olympic bars, other assorted bars, bumper plates). The gym advertised Eleiko bars but apparently it's only during manned hours (I saw staff taking 2 of them out slightly before 9am), and they are PL bars (was hoping for WL bars). Out of the 6 regular bars, only 1 spins well.

Despite the equipment, there were multiple signs prohibiting slamming of weights, even with bumpers and platforms, so I don't think management would take kindly to weightlifting. Machines are placed very near one another too, and the warmup/stretching area is tiny, and also no studio for classes. Lastly, there's a Life Fitness kinetic rower which I thought was a really dumb idea, because in order to even turn the rower on, you have to keep pulling it (apparently it runs off the kinetic energy generated from pulling). I had the rower die on me twice while trying to just set up a session, and before I even started my session I must've rowed  a few dozen times. The resistance is also adjusted by a knob that goes clockwise or anticlockwise, but doesn't show you what resistance it's currently at so there's no way of knowing. Why so many AF outlets get all sorts of weird indoor rowers instead of just getting C2 rowers, I'll never know...

There are showers but no sink or toilets, so if you need to wash your hands or use the toilet, you'll have to walk 2 min to the toilet outside.
Crowd wise, I was surprised to see the racks all being used at 7am, but they were free by the time I was done with warmup. Strangely, most of the free weights were being used by ladies rather than men. While that was a welcome sight, c'mon men, we can do better.

author: Rui Ren
text: Been coming to this outlet more recently and the vibe here makes me wanting to come back more! Very good gym equipment and facilities, and learned that are in partnership with ReFormd Personal Training!!

author: Terry Samuels
text: Rather impressed despite the crowd. Instructors were nice and genuine. A weird dude was using the machines dangerously, when informed, they approached him nicely.

author: Farhan Lim
text: My first time coming to this Anytime Fitness branch earlier today, no crowd, maybe bcuz its in the morning. The gym is super neat and clean. Good aircon and ventilation. I was mind blown to see a protein vending machine however alot of flavours sold out (i am sure it is a popular, high traffic gym in the evening), so i asked the staff Anwa if they were gonna top-up and have it available. Anwa was very nice and also explained to me how it works so bought one serving from the vending machine and we chatted for a bit. Seems like an amazing gym with fantastic location which is so convenient for some ppl cuz MRT is on B1! When i left the gym there was another staff who smiled and greeted her goodbye see you again to me! So comforting to see such warm service. I am coming here again tomorrow for sure!!

author: Nikki
text: Yulun at Reformd AF orchard is a good staff that helped me out with queries on membership as well as gave a detailed overview of the gym. I highly recommend everyone to come down and try this gym üëçüèª ‚Ä¶

author: Elisabeth
text:
I‚Äôve generally had a positive experience at this gym, but recently, mall management implemented a baffling new policy‚Äîturning off the air conditioning from 10:30 PM to 10:30 AM. This decision has significantly impacted the gym environment, making workouts not only uncomfortable but also unsafe.

With Singapore‚Äôs already high temperatures and humidity, the lack of proper ventilation leads to excessive sweating, making machines slippery and increasing the risk of injury. A gym should be a space that encourages people to push their limits safely, not one that discourages attendance due to poor conditions.

I urge management to reconsider this policy, as it negatively affects the gym experience and potentially endangers members. Maintaining a cool, well-ventilated workout space is not a luxury‚Äîit‚Äôs a necessity.

author: Joshua Nair
text: The most premium feel I've had in an Anytime Fitness. Good selection of machines / equipment and a thoughtful seating area. Machines are very close to each other though, so being polite and considerate is expecially important. Everyone was nice in my first visit today.

author: Angel Lee
text: Great gym with excellent facilities and a welcoming atmosphere. The equipment is well-maintained, and the space is clean and comfortable for workouts. The staff are friendly, helpful, and always ready to assist. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a convenient and well-equipped gym in Orchard!

author: dvxhupe
text: staff here very friendly and chill always says ‚Äúhi, welcome‚Äù when i came to the gym.  i love it and the place here is quite chill.

author: Sylvester
text:
In a city where the sweltering heat is already a formidable foe, one would expect a reputable gym like OC Anytime Fitness to provide a sanctuary of sorts ‚Äì a cool, refreshing oasis where one can escape the oppressive temperatures and focus on their fitness journey. Alas, dear reader, this is not the case.

Upon entering the gym during morning hours, I was immediately struck by the stifling air, thick with the stench of sweat and stagnation. It's as if the very walls were exhaling a collective sigh of despair. The reason for this sauna-like atmosphere? The gym's steadfast agreement to only turn on the air conditioning that follows the building's designated schedule.

And don't even get me started on the staff's apparent lack of initiative to provide even the most basic form of ventilation. A simple opening of the door, carefully monitored to ensure security, would have gone a long way in alleviating the suffocating atmosphere. But no, that would require too much effort, and apparently, that's too much to ask.

To add insult to injury, OC Anytime Fitness sees no need to inform its members about this egregious situation through social media or any other means. It's as if they're will-fully ignoring the problem, hoping that their patrons will simply suffer in silence. This is a gym that seems more concerned with following arbitrary rules than with providing a decent, comfortable experience for its members.

author: Darren Teo
text: This gym is well ventilated and equipped with state-of-the-art equipment. Lovely place to train with good vibes and music. Staff is also very friendly and easy to talk to :)

author: Êùé‰ª≤Áßã

author: Descloud 86
text:
I‚Äôve been a regular at AF Orchard but lately, the conditions have become unbearable. The mall has switched off the air conditioning, leaving the gym with no ventilation. The result? Stuffy, humid air, excessive condensation on the equipment, and an overall unpleasant workout environment.

The condensation makes machines and weights wet and slippery, which is not only frustrating but also a serious safety hazard. On top of that, with no airflow, body odor lingers in the gym, making the experience even worse. It‚Äôs nearly impossible to get through a workout comfortably.

A gym should provide a clean, safe, and comfortable environment for its members. Unfortunately, this gym is failing at all three. Until management fixes the air circulation and improves hygiene, I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this place to anyone.

author: A Lee

author: Hong Ee 18
text:
I‚Äôve been to a lot of gyms, but AF orchards stands out from the rest. From the moment you walk in, the energy is electric, and the vibe is so motivating! The equipment is top-notch, with a variety of machines and free weights for every kind of workout. Whether you're a beginner or a seasoned lifter, you'll find everything you need.

The trainers here are next-level ‚Äì super knowledgeable and genuinely invested in helping you reach your goals. They take the time to tailor workouts to your fitness level and push you in the best way possible. üí•

The group classes? üî• Whether it's high-intensity circuits, yoga, or spin, the classes are challenging but fun, and the community vibe is incredible. It feels like everyone is cheering each other on.

The best part is the cleanliness and organization. Everything is spotless, and the equipment is always ready to go ‚Äì no long waits or broken machines.

If you're looking for a gym that pushes you to be your best while feeling like part of a fitness family, AF orchard is the place to be. Highly recommend! üíØüèãÔ∏è‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

Aside from her exceptional professionalism, Dian's positive energy and friendly demeanor created a welcoming atmosphere that made every visit to the gym enjoyable. Her passion for fitness and genuine care for members like myself truly set her apart.

text:
I was thrown out of the gym! because I did not bring my fob key. In my defense, I have been allowed goodwill access to the gym in the past multiple times and have been lulled into complacency, and was somehow never told that I would be thrown out/ denied access. In AFO‚Äôs defense, they are perfectly entitled to do so according to the T&C first paragraph. Nonetheless I felt shamed and dismayed and after escalating and appealing at length to the floor manager Farah, she allowed me a ten minute workout.
To be fair this was a single occurrence. Some staff are really warm and friendly while others are nonchalant. Fellow gym users are generally polite and respectful; I‚Äôve had no bad interactions in the past one year. Gym gets awfully crowded but between 11-4 I almost always had my pick of machines. Affordable.

The only thing I would say is that sometimes the gym equipment and cleaning supplies aren't as well maintained. There was once the leg press was out for a week. The cleaning cloths and sprays sometimes don't work (wear and tear) and given it's 24-hour but the staff won't always be there, the weights and machine attachments can sometimes be just jumbled up.

All in all, the gym is still worth it if you like the flexibility to be able to workout any time in the heart of the city.

author: shilpa shastry
text:
Finding this place was a thrilling moment for me since this was exactly what I was looking for. A 24 hour full fledged gym which is spacious and right in the middle of orchard. A great place to workout which is also very well maintained.

I was also lucky to find a great personal trainer in Herzy. A personal trainer is not only the one who guides and motivates you to give your best during a workout session, but he is the expert who should know the workings of the body, the bones and the muscles. Herzy is all of that and more. He fully understands your requirement and accordingly customises your workout to suit your current needs and future goals. - Mid sized, not gigantic but sufficient
- Has an inclined Leg Press to put on 200kg+

Cons
- Lacking in some machines, but only very specific ones like Tricep Seated station etc, besides that you're fine
- Can be crowded since its in the middle of Orchard (even at late night)
- No vending machine at my time of visit, but then again you got food options in the mall
- Didn't visit the showers or baths, unknown if they have them though.

I visit here once in a while if I'm passing by and on the way to work for a quick workout, but will stick to my usual locations for less people

Good if you're on vacation and an AF member I guess

text:
Second time in the gym and will never visit again. I was asked to leave bcoz I wear my KEEN shoes to do squat. The staff said it‚Äôs not ‚Äúproper gym shoes‚Äù for workout. And it has never happened before for other anytime fitness branch I went to ( Kovan/ tanjong pagar etc). When I asked them if there‚Äôs any written rules or policy i can refer to, they cannot answer me and said it‚Äôs basic gym manner, and it will increase my ‚Äúinjury rate‚Äù.

The other 2 guys beside me were deadlifting with barefoot which I think it‚Äôs fine. And the staff asked them to wear their running shoes to do deadlift ! If ur reason is to reduce injury, I believe if u stand on running shoes and do deadlift will make ur injury rate higher‚Ä¶.if the staff really know what‚Äôs weightlifting.

I asked the deadlift guy if he was told to wear shoes when deadlift in other gym, he also said never. He just joined this gym and felt very weird.

So other people wear converse/ vans are considered proper gym footwear ? I don‚Äôt know their logic.

Will never visit again for sure.
